<item>
            <title>[BEAM-8188] pyarrow imports should be guarded with try/except</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-8188</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;pyarrow has elaborate requirements to target platform, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-6287&quot; title=&quot;pyarrow is not supported on Windows Python 2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BEAM-6287&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BEAM-6287&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-8181&quot; title=&quot;Beam fails to install on Windows machine with 32bit interpreters due to pyarrow requirements.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BEAM-8181&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BEAM-8181&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rather than repeating them through the codebase, we should attempt to import and fail gracefully. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cc: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=udim&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;udim&quot;&gt;udim&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=heejong&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;heejong&quot;&gt;heejong&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ostrokach&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ostrokach&quot;&gt;ostrokach&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
